This paper discusses the use of storage bricks as database servers for large datasets, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of Ethernet for data transmission suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions software issues, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or information theory (cs.IT).
